          {
            "commit": "d62efba975d27d98f2d50f14d49dda53d2355d0c",
            "subject": "LU-8837 utils: make tools lightweight for lustre clients"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "paf@cray.com",
          "date": "2017-08-21 09:45:05.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-11-22 03:55:16.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-9894 lfsck: Print correct lfsck start info",
        "message": "LU-9894 lfsck: Print correct lfsck start info\n\nWhen printing which scan type was started, lfsck iterates\nthrough an array of types and compares the given type to\nthe types in the array.  Type numbers are a bit mask.\n\nHowever, LFSCK_TYPES_SUPPORTED and LFSCK_TYPES_DEF are the\nfull mask, and they are the first in the array.  This means\nwe always match LFSCK_TYPES_SUPPORTED, which results in\nalways printing \"all\" as the type of scan.\n\nReorder the struct to increasing bit order to fix this.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial testlist=sanity-scrub,sanity-lfsck\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <paf@cray.com>\nChange-Id: Ibc82369ff6531b56ceda4b1c0a833720dc61f3f4\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/28604\nReviewed-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: James Nunez <james.a.nunez@intel.com>\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
  "requirements": [],
  "submit_records": []
